Objective: The main aim is to present some results from long-term observations of the crown and structural dynamics in thinned pure beech stand. In today's changing environment the knowledge on the dynamics of crowns is gaining more importance because tree crowns define the way that trees react to new enviromental conditions, or the applied silvicultural measures, e. g. thinnings.
Name: Daruvar - Vrani kamen
Data: dbh; height; hd; trunk lenght; horizontal projection of tree crown
Organisation: Croatian Forest Research Institute

Objective: In the frame of IUFRO programme Croatia have started, among numerous European countries, with the establishment of provenance tests with the aim of research on adaptability of valuable foreign species.
Name: Pilot object Lokve
Species: Picea abies; Pinus sylvestris; Pinus nigra; Pinus strobus; Pseudotsuga menziesii; Larix decidua
Data: height; dbh; volume; biomass production
Organisation: Croatian Forest Research Institute
References: Orlić S, Ocvirek M (1993) Growth of domestic and foreign conifer species in young cultures on fernery and heath areas of Croatia. Radovi, Vol. 28, BR. 1-2,:91-103, Jastrebarsko; Orlić S, Ocvirek M (1994): Research in provenances of Douglas Fir (Pseudotsuga menziesii (Mirb.) Franco) in Croatia. Ekologia (1335-342X) 23 (1) 86-98; Perić S, Seletković I, Medak J, Pilaš I, Topić, V. (2006.): Research of thriving of six coniferous species in ecologically characteristic regions of Croatia, Rad. Šumar. Inst. Izvanredno izdanje 9: 99-108, Jastrebarsko.

Objective: The goal of this research is to expand knowledge about the state of structure and ability of natural regeneration in protected stands of beech and fir. These stands are excluded from all regular silvicultural activities. A special observance will be given to the appearance of the young generation. We try to point out the real state of tree crown damage and to compare the results of stand quality with managed forests.
Name: National park "Risnjak"
Data: dbh; height; lenght of tree trunk; crown length; stem density; basal area; volume
Organisation: Croatian Forest Research Institute
References: Dubravac T, Dekanić S, Matošević D, Roth V (2008) Regeneration dynamics of uneven-aged forest stand after the establishment of national park 'Risnjak' and the abandonment of the management activities. International Conference Forestry in achieving millenium goals, Proceedings / Orlović, Saša (ur.). - Novi Sad : Institute of lowland forestry and environment, 309-317; Dubravac T, Medak J, Županić M (2014)  Forest-silviculture research in national parka "Risnjak" and "Plitvice lakes" in Croatia. Zbornik sažetaka broj1/2014. Drugi naučno-stručni skup sa međunarodnim sudjelovanjem 5 juni – Svjetski dan zaštite okoliša / Makić, Halid, Bećiraj, Azra, Ibrahimpašić, Jasmina, Džafarević, Aida, Talić, Mersija (ur.). - Bihać, Univerzitet u Bihaću, Biotehnički fakultet, 75-76.

Objective: The aim of the research through the repeated measurments is to estimate the stand structure development on the Medveđak permanent experimental plot in the Plitvice Lakes national park area
Name: National park "Plitvica Lakes"
Data: dbh; height; hd; horizontal projection of tree crown
Organisation: Croatian Forest Research Institute
References: Dubravac, T., Krejči, V., Vrbek, B. (2004.): State of the Structure and Possibility of Natural Reforestation of Pure Beech Stands in the "Medvjeđak" Forest Reservation. Objective: This plot was established for the purpose of monitoring the natural course of development of planted stand.The plot was used to monitor the natural stand structure development and reforestation of the stand.
Name: Delnice
Data: dbh; hd; horizontal projection of tree crown; height; crown diameter; height of crown base; tree coordinates; density and structure of regeneration; comparison of chemical and physical characteristics of soils between the plantation, natural stand and meadow
Organisation: Croatian Forest Research Institute
References: Dubravac T, Vrbek B, Benko M, Vuletić D, Littvay T (2005) Results of Fifty Years of Monitoring the Growth and Development of a 161 Year Old Norway Spruce Culture, The International Forestry Review. Periodicum biologorum 110(2): 187-193.

Objective: The aim was to present some general results on stand structure development of an old Norway spruce plantation and processes of succession in conditions of delayed stand reforestation and absence of management interventions during the course of a long management period, and to discuss the practice and experience of Central andWest Europe in regeneration and conversion of spruce plantations.
Name: Gorski kotar - Risnjak
Data: dbh; height; crown diameter; height of crown base; tree coordinates; horizontal crown projections; density and structure of regeneration; comparison of chemical and physical characteristics of soils between the plantation, natural stand and meadow
Organisation: Croatian Forest Research Institute
References: Čavlović J, Dubravac T, Roth V, Dekanić S, Teslak K (2008)Development of the stand structure of a 161-Year-old Norway spruce plantation, PERIODICUM BIOLOGORUM, Vol. 110, No 2, 187–193

Objective: Since the autumn of 1998, measurements of heights and registration of survival has been carried out. So far investigations of Common beech variability in Croatia (survival of plants, heights and increments, flushing) indicate that genetic differentiation exists, which is determined by numerous ecological factors.
